706931f-a.text:
Sumner Pl. near s.e. corner ofFlushing Ave., B'klyn.
Sept. 25, 1341
P.L. Sperr, photographer
706931f-a.folder: Sumner Place & Flushing Avenue, Brooklyn, NY

704394f-a.text:
(1)
796-800 Flushing Ave., south side, between Sumner Place and Fayette Street. The house standing back from the street is an extensien of the Charles De Bevoise heuse (built in 1836) the main portien of which stood on the site of No. 796. The German branch of the Y.M.C.A., erganized in 1878, purchased the old homestead in 1885 and used it until merged with
the main Williamsburg Y.M.C.A.
About 19221
Eugene L. Armbruster Cellection.
(2)
The same, another view.
September 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
